  "description": [
    "Magsaysay Wins Presidency Of Phillipines MANILA UPTired ailing Pres ident Elpidio Quirino Thursday conceded victory in the Philip pines presidential election to the youthful vigorous Ramon Mag saysay who won in a landslide The 46yearold CommunistHuk fighter a staunch friend of the United States becomes the third President of this sevenyearold republic He is to take office on Jan 1 for a fouryear term Quir ino steps out after six years in office Magsaysay was cruising in Man ila Bay on the palatial yacht of Adm Richard H Cruzen com mander of US Naval forces in the Phillipines when word that Quirion had conceded reached him Over the yachts radio telephone Magsaysay said he was profound ly grateful to our people for the overwhelming expression of their confidence in our cause Reds Work On Air Bases Of US But No Sabotage WASHINGTON UPtSen Case RSD said Thursday French and British Communists are helping build US air bases abroad but there has been no sabotage and none is expected There is no way to screen out Communist workers in England and France on military projects there he said and added I was told that many of the workers are called Communists"
